**Business Overview & Niche:** FoodCycle is a UK-based national charity with a distinct dual-mission niche. Its business is to combat two major social issues simultaneously: **food waste and social isolation**. It operates by collecting surplus food from retailers and suppliers, then using volunteer power to prepare and serve nutritious community meals in a warm, welcoming environment. Its unique value proposition lies in this interconnected modelâ€”addressing environmental sustainability (food waste) through direct social action (alleviating hunger and loneliness). Its niche is community dining as a vehicle for holistic social and environmental impact.

## âš¡ Quick Summary
FoodCycle is a UK charity that tackles food waste, hunger, and loneliness through a single, powerful model. It transforms surplus food into community meals, creating spaces for connection and support. Its core proposition is using food as a tool for both environmental sustainability and social cohesion.

